        <div1 type="summary">
            <p><add hand="#barker">Introducing James Burnet. Numbers moving to join you.</add></p>
        </div1>
        <div1 type="body">
            

<p><placeName>Nackitosh </placeName><date when="1821-12-26">Decr 26th 1821.</date></p>
<p>Dear Sir</p>

<p>The <persName>Bearer </persName><persName>Mr. James Burnet of Pearl River</persName> has Just called upon
me on his way to <placeName>St. Antonio</placeName>; he has a letter from the <persName>Governor
Poindexter [Mississippi.]</persName> to all the facts there stated I can subscribe
having been acquainted with him, his <persName>Father </persName>and <persName>family </persName>for near
Twenty years - I have no news to write you, the <placeName>Papers </placeName>since you
left us are barren I have sent such as I had to the <persName>Baron Bastrop</persName>, I
shall be in <placeName>N. Orleans</placeName> in a few days, and if I can hear of anything
Interesting I shall not fail to communicate it.</p>

<p><persName>Mr Burnet</persName> will tell you of the numbers moving to Join you he is
waiting</p>

<p><persName>John Sibley</persName>    [Rubric]</p>

<p>[Addressed:] <persName>Stephen F. Austin Esquire</persName> <placeName>Colerado Mr. Burnet</placeName></p>


        </div1>
